Weekly_Review:_Apr.13_--_Apr.19
At least 11 killed, 50 injured in a fire in C China
2013-04-14 08:35:06 GMT
At least 5 were killed and 20 injured in a fire accident Sunday morning in Xiangyang, Hubei province, C China.The fire broke out around 6 am from a netbar and rapidly spread to the hotel upstairs, the district government said.People were seen hiding from the fire standing oustide of the building wall. Some of them even jumped from the 4th floor to escape, according to witnesses' photos.The fire was extinguished at 8:50 am. The injured have been sent to local hospitals to receive treatment.The cause of the fire is under investigation.
